        <div class="section-label">About</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Hello.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about">
      <div class="about-prose">
        <p class="lede">
          I'm Tae Young. Most people call me TY. I go by <span class="mono">@ty2035</span> online.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm 14. I live in Seoul and I'm in middle school. I make games on
          <a href="https://playentry.org/profile/ty2035" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Entry</a>,
          design interfaces in Figma, and write websites in HTML and CSS and a bit of JavaScript.
          This is my corner of the internet.
        </p>
        <p>
          I think I like making things mostly because it's the opposite of homework.
          Nobody tells you what it should look like. Nobody grades it. You just keep going
          until it feels right.
        </p>
        <p>
          I care about small details — the way a button feels when you press it,
          the space between two lines of text, whether a color is slightly too loud.
          Most of what I'm learning is how to trust when something is done.
        </p>
      </div>

